#Text=Santa
#Text=Clara ( California )
#Text=Santa
#Text=Clara
#Text=is a town in the South Bay , part of the San Francisco Bay Area , in California .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Santa Clara is a small city of big contrasts .
#Text=If any city can claim to be " the center of Silicon Valley , " it is this town of just over 100,000 .
#Text=Intel , AMD , WebEx , NVIDIA , and National Semiconductor all have headquarters here .
#Text=At the same time , Santa Clara is one of the oldest settlements ( by Europeans ) in Northern California .
#Text=The Mission Santa Clara de Asís was established in 1777 , and the Jesuit-run Santa Clara University , founded in 1851 , is the oldest university in California .
#Text=Dozens of 19th-century homes are well-maintained by their 21st-century owners in the " old quad , " the earliest residential area , adjacent to the university .
#Text=Yet another contrast is the diversity of the local population , driven by the tech boom of the 1970s-1990s .
#Text=Visitors from Asia and Europe frequently overhear strangers speaking their native languages .
#Text=Specialty markets offer native ingredients from around the world , and the Indian and East Asian restaurants are some of the best in the Bay Area .
#Text=But many of the best places in Santa Clara are not visible at first glance .
#Text=You could drive right through this town and see nothing of any interest , or you could take the time to learn where to look , explore , and enjoy .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Just west of San Jose , Santa Clara is adjacent to San Jose Mineta Airport ( SJC ) .
#Text=To reach the airport take the free shuttle from the Santa Clara Caltrain station , route 10 .
#Text=To the San Francisco International Airport , take Caltrain north ( toward San Francisco ) to Millbrae .
#Text=From there , transfer to BART and take BART to San Bruno and then to SFO .
#Text=Allow about an hour and a half .
#Text=The Oakland International airport is accessible by via the Coliseum/Oakland Airport BART station and the AirBART shuttle .
#Text=From Amtrak , transfer to BART at Jack London Square .
#Text=By train
#Text=Caltrain
#Text=stops at Santa Clara Station , on the east side of Santa Clara University ( 1001 Railroad Avenue ) .
#Text=Though Caltrain does n't really stop at San Jose Mineta Airport , the free Airporter bus ( VTA line 10 ) shuttles passengers between the airport and the Santa Clara Caltrain station .
#Text=The Altamont Commuter Express ( ACE ) is an Amtrak express train running from the central valley towns of Stockton , Tracy , Livermore and Pleasanton to San Jose .

#Text=The train shares the Santa Clara station with Caltrain and also stops at the Great America station at Lafayette and Tasman , near the Santa Clara Convention Center , Levi 's Stadium , and California 's Great America .
#Text=Only a few trains run per day .
#Text=The Great America stop does n't include a station building , just a platform under an overpass , so plan connecting transportation before you arrive .

#Text=When you get off the southbound ACE train at Great America in the morning , there are free shuttle buses waiting to take you to destinations throughout Silicon Valley ( as far away as the offices of Google in the west , Cisco in the east , and Nvidia in the south ) .
#Text=Similar shuttles run in the reverse direction in the afternoon/evening .
#Text=Amtrak
#Text=California 's Capitol Corridor train runs between Sacramento and San Jose via East Bay cities such as Berkeley and Emeryville .
#Text=The Capitol Corridor shares the same stations as the ACE above , stopping at the University and Great America .
#Text=The nearby Diridon Station in San Jose includes a building with a ticket counter and may even be closer to parts of Santa Clara .
#Text=Read schedules carefully , since some trains include a bus connection .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Light rail and bus
#Text=.
#Text=The Valley Transportation Authority ( VTA ) offers light rail in Santa Clara on the Alum Rock-Santa Teresa and Mountain View-Winchester lines .
#Text=VTA also offers bus service within and around Santa Clara .
#Text=Consult the VTA website for schedules , fares , and trip planning .
#Text=Rental car
#Text=.
#Text=Numerous national car rental chains serve Santa Clara and surrounding cities .
#Text=Most people living in the area prefer automobiles as their primary means of transportation , and it is likely to be the fastest , although area freeways do get congested during commute hours .
#Text=Rental cars are available both at the San Jose Airport and at various locations in the city .
#Text=Throughout most of Santa Clara , public parking is ample and free .
#Text=Bicycle
#Text=.

#Text=Many city streets are wide and bicycle-friendly with painted bicycle lanes ; expressways permit bicycles but have high-speed , heavy traffic that may be uncomfortable , especially for inexperienced riders .
#Text=Stop by City Hall for a copy of the Santa Clara bicycle map showing recommended bicycle routes .
#Text=Bicycles should ride on the right side of the road , going the same direction as traffic .
#Text=Take care when crossing expressway exits and right turn lanes in traffic .
#Text=Caltrain , Amtrak Capital Corridor , and VTA ( both light rail and buses ) are all equipped with bicycle racks .
#Text=If you plan to take a bicycle on area public transit , consult the website of the system(s) you will use for information on locating and using the bicycle racks .
#Text=See
#Text=Intel Museum
#Text=Mission College Blvd ( off Montague expressway , just north of 101 ) .
#Text=M - F 9AM-6PM ; Sa 10AM-5PM .
#Text=Learn a bit of local and technological history , and see what it takes to enter a cleanroom .
#Text=Allow 1 – 2 hours .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Mission Santa Clara
#Text=, 500 El Camino Real ( on the Santa Clara University campus ) , ☏ +1408 554-4023 , fax : +1408 551-7166 .
#Text=The eighth Franciscan California mission , founded by Father Serra .
#Text=It was built nearer to the Guadalupe River , moved to its present location in 1828 , and restored in 1929 .
#Text=It is the only mission on a university campus .

#Text=In front of the church , see the hitching ring and step for dismounting from a carriage ; peer through the fence into the rose garden on the north side of the church ; measure the life-sized statue of Fr .

#Text=Serra , stroll along the walkway covered with gnarled wisteria vines , into the Mission Gardens with the giant sago palm , Sacred Heart Statue , adobe wall ( with a hole for cooking ) , grinding stone .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Santa Clara University
#Text=, 500 El Camino Real , ☏ +1408 554-4000 .
#Text=If driving , be aware of campus parking restrictions .
#Text=de Saisset Museum
#Text=, 500 El Camino Real ( on the Santa Clara University grounds near Palm and Alviso streets ) .
#Text=Tu - Su 11AM - 4PM .
#Text=The museum combines rotating exhibitions with a permanent collection of works by Ernest de Saisset , a 19th-century Santa Clara student who studied painting in Paris .
#Text=The museum is often closed between exhibitions , so call ahead or check the website for open dates .
#Text=Agnews Developmental Center
#Text=, 4030-4070 Lafayette St ( just off the Montague Expressway ) .
#Text=The Agnews Historic Park preserves three buildings from the old California Hospital for the Chronic Insane .
#Text=Founded in 1889 , the facility 's original buildings collapsed in the " San Francisco Earthquake " of 1906 , killing 117 people .

#Text=The new buildings , including the still-standing auditorium , clock tower and superintendent 's residence , are good examples of early twentieth century Mediterranean Revival architecture , heavily influenced by the Arts and Crafts style .
#Text=The new buildings represented a more modern attitude toward the mentally ill .
#Text=The smaller buildings with larger windows were designed to comfort and stimulate the mentally ill , rather than imprison them .

#Text=The state of California moved the last few hundred residents out in the mid 1990s , and sold the campus to Sun Microsystems , who promised to preserve the grounds and buildings , and make the auditorium and executive mansion available for public events .

#Text=Unfortunately , you cannot get inside to see the very impressive interiors of the buildings , unless you 've got a Sun employee badge or are lucky enough to slip in during a meeting or public event .
#Text=Neither tours nor docents seem to be available .
#Text=You can visit a small shelter that has public restrooms , as well as historic photographs and information about the hospital .
#Text=Triton Museum of Art
#Text=, 1505 Warburton . Tu - Su .
#Text=The museum offers a variety of rotating exhibits .
#Text=Classes and special events may require a fee . Free .
#Text=Harriss-Lass Historic Museum
#Text=, 1889 Market St. Sa Su only noon-4PM . This 19th-century farmhouse has been restored and converted to a museum of local history , complete with many of the original furnishings .
#Text=opening hours may be subject to volunteer docent availability .
#Text=KoreaTown
#Text=.

#Text=Though not yet officially recognized , the area of El Camino beginning at Lawrence Expressway and extending east to San Tomas Expressway is home to many Korean-owned businesses , stores , and restaurants .
#Text=South Bay Historical Railroad Society
#Text=Tu 5-8PM , Sa 10AM-3PM .
#Text=This museum occupies the historical Santa Clara railway depot building near the Santa Clara Caltrain station .
#Text=It features a variety of historical railroad artifacts and elaborate model railroads at HO and N scales .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Santa Clara City Hall

#Text=Warburton Ave. The grounds surrounding City Hall include a statue of Santa Clara , fountains , " Stroll Into the Past " plaques , other public artwork , and a set of flagpoles featuring all the flags that have flown over Santa Clara .
#Text=Inside City Hall hangs a collection of historical photographs .
#Text=City Hall is across the street from the Triton Museum and worth a stroll around the grounds if you are visiting the museum .
#Text=Old Quad
#Text=.

#Text=Roughly , this is the area outlined by El Camino Real , Lafayette , Market , and Lincoln streets , and it makes up the old , historical section of the city . Many 19th-century homes are well preserved .

#Text=If you have time , explore this area by bicycle or on foot , and make time to visit the local historical buildings , such as the Harris-Lass museum and the Women 's Club Adobe , that are in and around the Old Quad .
#Text=Agnews Historic Cemetery and Museum
#Text=Phone for appointment .

#Text=Opened in 2010 , the museum honors people that worked and lived at the Agnews State Hospital and later Agnews Developmental Center from 1888 to 2009 with artifacts and photos and a viewing area for the restored cemetery .
